o the conclusion that since elephants\u2019 frequently used routes and corridor had been blocked by the expansion of the Camp, the animals could be moving move around the camp along its border. To prove this hypothesis, IUCN\u2019s field survey started on 31 January 2018, engaging a team of 14 staff and volunteers. The survey team was duly oriented about the field situation, the Camp condition, Elephant foot-prints close to the Camp 3 \u00a9 IUCN/ M. A. Motaleb Page | 13 and were made aware of other precautions that", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "2e3e8498-4b7e-4b2d-b0ed-814baa8a2bb9": {"__data__": {"id_": "2e3e8498-4b7e-4b2d-b0ed-814baa8a2bb9", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/survey-report-elephant-movement-human-elephant-conflict-situation-and", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Survey report on elephant movement, human-elephant conflict situation, and possible intervention sites in and around Kutupalong Camp, Cox's Bazaar", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/survey-report-elephant-movement-human-elephant-conflict-situation-and", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "46052e55253fce152f78c7af2999ad6efcdc1e6d88f53bad373bea5086f761c6"}, "3": {"node_id": "aeb426e9-3585-4849-8b06-77950e62d7e7", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/survey-report-elephant-movement-human-elephant-conflict-situation-and", "Author": "International Un